\Abstract{
  The aim of this paper is to investigate how a countries decision to join one or all of the steps leading towards the common European currency changed its inflation rate dynamics. Our attempt is to model the inflation rates via a Generalized Logistic Distribution and then test for breaks in the parameters of mean, variance and skewness.
}

\Keywords{inflation rate, structural break, EMU, Generalized Logistic Distribution, EURO}


