\subsection{Belgium and Luxembourg}

On the basis of these results, we are able to trace out different groups. The first of this group consits of Belgium and Luxembourg. This may come as no surprise since both countries formed a monetary union prior even to the start of the Exchange Rate Mechanism (ERM). While both countries enjoyed very stable inflation rates with low values of both mean and variance, this changed around the timing of the irrevocable fixing of the exchange rates. A causal connection to this events seems likely.

% interesting thing: both were allready in a currency union (the belgish--luxembourg union)

