We find a break in August 2003 d with a much lower mean value (only a third now of its previous value) and interestingly enough, a higher volatility. The supLM test graph on the right hand side suggests one break around 2003 and possibly another towards the end of the sample. This second break point is not estimated, since we restricted a regime towars a length of at least 24 month. \\
Slovenia did achieve this by two very important measures. First it liberalized the financial markets in 2003 and -- most important -- it restricted the year--on--year growth of the monetary base M1 severely starting in 2003. Combined these were enough to ensure  Slovenian participation in the EURO--zone.


